Professional Thief
The Professional Thief is a skilled criminal specializing in theft, burglary,
and the quiet removal of valuables. They are not brawlers; they rely on
speed, skill, and planning to get in and out without confrontation.

Professional Thieves choose from Rogue, Espionage, Technical, and Physical
skill categories. Their lock-picking, sleight of hand, and surveillance
evasion skills are unmatched among criminal OCCs.

Attribute requirements: IQ 10, PP 12.
Starting equipment: Lock pick set, concealed sidearm, dark civilian clothing,
grappling hook and line, personal radio, and a modest credit reserve from
recent work.
